  static const String theoryText_3_3 =
      '''To achieve a balance between risk and return in investments, many investors employ a portfolio diversification strategy. Diversification involves spreading investments across different assets, markets, and sectors to reduce risks and increase potential returns. For example, instead of investing the entire amount in one company, an investor may distribute their investments among stocks of different companies, bonds from various issuers, and so on.\n
In conclusion, risk and return are integral parts of investments. Investors should understand that a high level of risk may be associated with high returns, but it also comes with the potential for investment loss. Proper planning, analysis, and portfolio diversification can help investors strike a balance between risk and return and achieve their financial goals.''';
  static const String theoryText_4_1 =
      '''The rules of portfolio diversification are an essential tool for investors seeking to reduce risks and enhance the potential return of their investments. Diversification involves allocating investments across various assets, markets, and sectors to decrease dependence on a specific asset or sector and mitigate potential losses.\n
  The first rule of portfolio diversification involves distributing investments across different asset classes. This means including various types of assets in the portfolio, such as stocks, bonds, real estate, etc. Each of these assets has its own characteristics and risks, and their combination can help reduce the overall level of risk.''';
  static const String theoryText_4_2 =
      '''The second rule of portfolio diversification is to allocate investments across different markets. Investors should consider investing not only in the local market but also in international markets. This can help mitigate risks associated with political and economic instability in a single country or region.\n
