  static const String theoryText_5_2 =
      '''Another important financial indicator is the company's liquidity. Investors should assess the company's ability to meet its current obligations and payments, as well as its potential to finance future projects and investments. Analyzing liquidity ratios, such as current ratio and quick ratio, allows investors to evaluate the financial stability of the company.\n
Additionally, investors should analyze the financial structure of the company. This involves assessing its level of debt and ability to pay interest on borrowings. Investors should focus on debt ratios, such as the debt-to-assets ratio and interest coverage ratio, to determine the level of risk associated with investing in the company.''';
  static const String theoryText_5_3 =
      '''It is also crucial to analyze the efficiency of the company's asset utilization. Investors should evaluate how efficiently the company uses its assets to generate profit. Analyzing indicators of asset utilization, such as asset turnover and return on assets, helps investors determine the growth potential and profitability of the company.\n
