  static const String theoryText_7_2 =
      '''Another crucial aspect of fundamental analysis is the evaluation of economic conditions and industry trends. Investors examine macroeconomic indicators such as GDP, inflation, and unemployment to determine the overall economic situation and its impact on the company. They also analyze industry trends, such as technological innovations and changes in consumer demand, to assess the prospects for the industry and the company.\n
To assess the value of assets and companies, investors use various methods such as discounted cash flow, price-to-earnings (P/E) ratio, price-to-book (P/B) ratio, and others. These methods enable investors to determine whether an asset or company is overvalued or undervalued in the market.''';
  static const String theoryText_7_3 =
